<br>
Let me spell it out for you in detail.<br>
<br>
Several weeks ago, a Japanese guild playing on a server with only Velious installed zerged the sleeper and got him to 24% - they made a video of it and installed it.  Now, up until that point, the sleeper had never been woken with a server wide effort.  The only servers that had a chance - like Xev - had had him woken by immature guilds seeking to make a name for themselves by showing they didn't care about the rest of the server.<br>
<br>
The folks on RZ got their idea from THAT encounter - not from any of their own thinking.  It didn't matter - they still organized and killed the sleeper.  Xev would have gotten the same idea from the same video - and probably would have been the first to give it a go.  The high end guilds on Xev have always been semi-civil.  Many of them had probably kicked around waking the sleeper several times before he actually was.  It wouldn't have been hard to organize and do.<br>
<br>
Now on to your facts:<br>
<br>
1) See above.  Yup - whoops, you lose.  RZ knew the sleeper was killable before engaging.  Time to get a new fact.<br>
<br>
2) Pure and utter nonsense.  First, see above for why Xev probably would have had a go before RZ.  Second, many of us still play everquest to beat seemingly impossible encounters.  Third, how many people do you see shunning FoH or TR?  AL did every encounter but Quarm first (and that only by the space of some 20 minutes or so).  Just because you are lame enough that its all about dick stroking doesn't mean the rest of EQ is.<br>
<br>
3) Why did older guilds complain?  Yeah, anyone could have done it.  The point was that it took cooperation between some of the largest competitors on the server NOT to do it.  That in itself means something.  It was never about the loot for many of us.  You sound just as selfish and immature as their actions that day when you spout BS crap like that then claim it is a &quot;fact&quot;.<br>
<br>
Just because you are too immature and selfish to see that EQ is a COMMUNITY as well as a game does not make it untrue.  Real people play are playing the characters around you.  They have real feelings and believe it or not, how you act can affect how they are feeling.  Noone likes to log onto a game for a bit of enjoyment and have some retard go out of his way to ruin their play time.  While I would be the first to say that it is just a game and you should remember that - I am also the first to say that you should remember that characters are real people and act accordingly.<br>
<br>
Also, you wont give anyone a whipping in a rant.  The only half decent efforts you've made have been jumping on the band wagon when others have already turned the target into a rotting carcass.<br>
